  "texts": [
    "Additionally, in the case of BC5CDR, it achieves correction rates close to 90% for spurious errors, highlighting its capability to properly filter out invalid entities.",
    "Although fine-tuned NER models show promising accuracy in in-distribution settings, i.e., the train and test data are sampled from the same dataset (or distribution), they can hardly be applied to unseen labels or shifted distribution, lacking robustness in out-of-distribution (OOD) settings.",
    "Thus, we investigate if our VERIFINER framework can also prove effectiveness in OOD scenarios, where finetuned models are trained on the datasets that are distinct from the test distribution.",
    "Unseen Distribution.",
    "We apply VERIFINER to the NER models fine-tuned on a source dataset, and evaluate it on a target dataset whose labels are not seen during the training (i.e., train on GENIA and infer on BC5CDR, and vice versa)."
